Okay, so I'm doing something a bit different. This isn't song lyrics or some random thing asking the general public about something or other. This is something serious for once. You might think it isn't, but, and those who know me well or have known me for a while will attest to this, it's something I've been debating for a while. And that would be:

Whether or not I should become a vegetarian.

And don't jump to any conclusions about me being an animal rights activist. I gave rats morphine. And made them swim while they were stoned (it's not as bad as it sounds; this occured in a lab, with supervision, and was regulated). So I'm not a PETA freak, although I am against animal testing in cosmetics, because hell, we need medicine more than we need makeup. We need medicine a LOT more.

But I'm digressing.

I'm not debating becoming a vegetarian because I think it's morally wrong to eat animals. Heck, I'm an omnivore, and under the right circumstances I'd have an El Gaucho Petite Filet Mignon once a week. And I LOVE bacon cheeseburgers. So why would I remotely consider giving up my favorite food group? Because ecologically we can't sustain my diet (those who've taken Cameron biology can skip the rest of this paragraph). Say I ate nothing but steak for a week. In order to feed enough cows so I could eat sufficient amounts of beef to support my lifestyle (energetically), those cows would need to be fed some sort of plant material (this obviously isn't including the intensively farmed cattle that are fed animal byproducts, that's another issue I have, but I'm not going into that further). Now if I gave up eating steak and only ate the plant material for a week, there'd be enough veggies and grains to feed not only me but nine other people for that week.

Think about it, if I'm eating mostly meat, which I do, how many people am I denying food? And I know that me becoming a vegetarian is not going to do much difference, since if I don't order that delicious looking steak, someone else will. But it's a start. Maybe I can influence people. And maybe I can cut down on the meat I eat rather than do away with it altogther. Because it'd be a shame to pass up a Double-Double with a Sidecar ("Sidecars are for bitches!"), or that 4x4 I said I'd eat, next time I'm at an In-N-Out.

So what do you think? What should I do?

God, I'm such a hippie somedays...

I haven't updated in a while, but this is important.

I'm back from Montana! Instead of giving you a huge review of how wonderful Glacier National Park, rafting, tubing, Howard's Pizza, and getting stung by a bee for the first time in my life were, I'm going to say one very important thing:

GO SEE AN INCONVENIENT TRUTH!!!

I don't care what your political affiliations are, if you can't suck it up and watch Al Gore for an hour and a half, read the screenplay. Analyze the statistics and form an opinion. But have one, one way or another, rather than live in ignorance.

"The Earth does not belong to us. We belong to the Earth."

And like parasites, we're destroying it.

I've been to Glacier National Park. There used to be 150 glaciers. Now there's 30. In about a quarter of a century, there may not be any left. And that's not the worst of it...

Will you just stand by and let it happen? Refuse to take action? Pretend global warming isn't your problem?

I won't.

Is this the New Year, or just another night?
Is this the new fear, or just another fright?
Is this the new tear, or just another desperation?
Is this the finger, or just another fist?
Is this the kingdom, or just a hit and miss?
I miss direction, most in all this desperation
Is this what they call freedom?
Is this what you call pain?
Is this what they call discontented fame?
It'll be a day like this one,
When the world caves in
When the world caves in
When the world caves in
I'm singing this one, like a broken piece of glass,
For broken arms and broken noses in the back
Is this the new year, or just another desperation?
You push until you're shoving,
You bend until you break,
Do you stand on the broken fields where your fathers lay?
It'll be a day like this one,
When the world caves in
When the world caves in
When the world caves in
When the world caves in, 
When the world caves in,
When the world caves in
There's nothing here worth saving,
There's no one here at all,
Is there any net left, that could break our fall?
It'll be a day like this one,
When the sky falls down,
And the hungry and poor and deserted are found
Are you discontented?
Have you been pushing hard?
Have you been throwing down, this broken house of cards?
It'll be a day like this one,
When the world caves in,
When the world caves in,
Is there nothing left now?
Nothing left to sing?
Are there any left now, who haven't kissed the enemy?
Is this the new year, or just another desperation?
Does justice ever find you?
Do the wicked never lose?
Is there any other song, to sing beside these blues?
And nothing is okay,
Til' the world caves in...
       ~ Jon Foreman
         Dec 31 2004

Happy New Year. I have no resolution. Suggestions? Maybe "Be Happy?"

Anyway, I received a Chocolate Fondue Kit and the Charlie and the Chocolate Factory Soundtrack. And the Lovely and Talented Mr. Depp was nominated for a Golden Globe. Therefore to get to the point, does anyone want to have a Golden Globe Party(as it is highly unlikely that Johnny will get the Oscar nod he deserves)? I'll make the fondue and provide music of course. And for those of us Johnny Depp diehards, perhaps a movie marathon before hand (homework depending!). January 16 to those interested.

I hate today.

Happy New Year's, baby, we could probably fix it if we cleaned it up all day...

Am back.

And for your New Year's Eve enjoyment. And because it seems fitting to me:

And its been a long December, and there's reason to believe
Maybe this year will be better than the last
I can't remember all the times I tried to tell myself
To hold on to these moments as they pass

I thought this year would turn out so differently. I was thinking earlier if I could go back and freeze time, what I would choose. Would it be this past spring break? Would it be before I moved? Would it be a concert/movie I liked? Would it be before Tramp died? Would it be before I was in school and life seemed like fun? Would it be this past May when I believed things would turn out better than they did?

Or would the May I choose be May 1988?

I wish I could communicate better. I never tell people what I want, because I think that it would mean more if they did so without knowing. Maybe that's why I'm always disappointed. 

Say you'll be with me when the heartache ends...
December promise she gave unto me December whisperings of treachery December clouds are now covering me December songs no longer I sing.

Caller: Well, this is your crazy old aunt! And it was indeed my great-aunt from Michy!. Apparently she tried to call my great-uncle in Montana, as it was his birthday. Wanda is apparently his girlfriend. So we were all amused. I found that post-worthy. Monday - NATIONAL TALK LIKE A BLOODY PIRATE DAY BUCKOS!!! And I am ready to hurt my iTunes. They keep playing "Blind." I love that song, but it is currently TIED with 'Everything" for most played. a. Break up with Brian
b. Severe ties completely with my parents
c. Keep going on and hope the pressure doesn't build up anymore than it already and pointlessly has.

So I guess this is the time to fly off into the switling brown of Saturn's methane rivers.

So they are now not only alphabetical by band/singer/group and chronological within said band/singer/group, but the CDs and jackets all match up! And I redid the structure, so instead of having jacket over CD or vice-versa, they are NEXT to each other. And I have 62 CDs (several of which I should get rid of) and a total of 759 songs. But only 161 on iTunes (including those I have borrowed from parental unit's CDs). Need to upload...

So then headed out with grandparents to meet parents at Henry's for dinner. Took bloody forever. Had good bacon-cheeseburger, and the bun had CHEESE in it. I love cheese. Fries good too. My dad asked how the burger ranked on my list, and I said after Stanich's and In-N-Out. And his (looked rather injured that I forgot to mention this at first). 

So got home. Find rather large pirate flag in window that parents bought when they went to the coast (not the beach, the coast) for the sole purpose of driving car to coast. So second thought was it was some crazy night prowler. Then remembered Brian was home, so thought it was him. Finished putting on PJs, and opened shades to discover that it WAS the crazy night prowler! Whose name was Brian, He-Who-Recently-Returned-From-His-Stay-With-the-White-Supremacists. So talked for a bit, in which I kept thinking "Crap, my parent's are going to be majorly P.O'd." Because I told them, and they were... are. So home, ended up not going to dance thing as there was no one to tag along with as "I wouldn't hang out with them." Then had long, in-depth discussion, forgot to eat almost, and invited Brian over. It was weird, because they talked more about the religious bit than the people at GU, and Gonzaga's a Catholic school. But I have a v. good chance at a scholarship there too, so not ruling it out.

Anyway, talked to the swim coach (one thing bad about GU, it only has club swimming), and he basically said I need to drop time if I want to contribute. Doesn't bother me to much, as I'd be going in as a young freshman or a REALLY, REALLY young sophmore.

2. Gonzaga (I was impressed. A lot more than a basketball team)
3. Whitworth (I'm not ruling it out, but the tour focused so much more on the Christianity aspect than the actual "This-is-the-place-you-will-be-learning-stuff" college stuff. But they're PIRATES, which is cool)
4. OSU (Ack. It be big)

<lj-cut text="And now a bit of a rant..."> So I'm interrupting my Friday update to rant. Yes, I do this occasionally. 

On both tours there were COUPLES touring. And at Whitworth there were only three students (including myself) touring. I can't stand that, I mean, it's great you've got someone and all, but you shouldn't base going to college solely on the fact that your boyfriend/girlfriend is going there. What if you break up and realize you don't LIKE the school? Yes, you can transfer, but it's still a lot of work that could have been avoided. This is part of why I have so vehemently opposed dating in high school (yeah, I'm currently a hypocrit. Sue me). Either you go to seperate colleges and split up, go to the same college and split up and then have to spend a lot of time with your new ex, or, my personal favorite, enroll in the same college and split up AFTER the May 1st deadline and end up going to a school that probably wasn't your first choice. But I'm not completely cynical, the whole thing could work out, but then it could probably work out regardless of whether or not you attended the same college, and if you split up going to the same college, you would have spilt up going to different colleges anyway. Bottom line: Don't pick a school based on who's going there. Stupid couples. </lj-cut>

Then shopped at Costco to kill time (bought spiffy sweatshirt!) and off to the person who got us our rabbits. She has SO many bunnies; they're so cute! And several cats (one was Omish; it had seven toes!). And she said she'd give me a job if I went to school there. Yes!
